1ed17730-10d4-463d-9324-6ab05923fb12	CorroHealth Backs UAE's SANTECHTURE to Drive AI-Led Transformation in Healthcare Revenue Management 	Article	\N	Abu Dhabi SME Hub	Published	2025-11-14 10:04:39.13+00	<p>UAE-based healthtech firm SANTECHTURE has received a strategic investment from US-headquartered CorroHealth, solidifying a two-year working relationship focused on bringing AI-powered innovations to healthcare revenue cycle management (RCM) in the Gulf region.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Founded by Anas Batikhi in 2019, SANTECHTURE delivers digital RCM and automation solutions to healthcare providers across the UAE, Saudi Arabia, India, and Egypt, supporting them in streamlining operations and enhancing patient-provider experiences.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Formalizing a Strategic Alliance</strong></p><p>This investment marks a key milestone in the collaboration between SANTECHTURE and CorroHealth, who have worked closely on piloting AI-based RCM solutions tailored to regional market needs. The two companies have jointly hosted events such as the Arab Health 2025 AI &amp; RCM Innovation Reception, and completed multiple proofs of concept for healthcare organizations in the region.</p><p>With the new partnership, SANTECHTURE is expected to enhance its offerings by integrating CorroHealth’s proprietary AI tools, helping hospitals and clinics in the GCC region optimize operational efficiency and protect revenue streams.</p><blockquote><p>“Combining our platform with CorroHealth’s advanced AI systems allows us to bring unmatched automation and insight to our clients,”&nbsp;</p></blockquote><p>said Anas Batikhi, Founder and CEO of SANTECHTURE.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Backed by Regional and Global Confidence</strong></p><p>SANTECHTURE is already backed by leading regional investors including Gulf Capital and Shorooq Partners, who previously invested in the company in 2023. The latest investment signals continued confidence in SANTECHTURE’s ability to lead digital transformation in the healthcare sector.&nbsp;</p><blockquote><p>“We’re proud to support this next chapter in SANTECHTURE’s growth,”&nbsp;</p></blockquote><p>said Mohammad Madani, Managing Director at Gulf Capital.&nbsp;</p><blockquote><p>“Partnering with a global player like CorroHealth is a major validation of the company’s leadership in intelligent RCM.”</p></blockquote><p>For CorroHealth, the move is part of a broader strategy to expand into international markets, particularly in the GCC.&nbsp;</p><blockquote><p>“This collaboration reflects our commitment to innovation and growth in the region,”&nbsp;</p></blockquote><p>said Bilal Mushtaq, EVP of Global Growth and Strategy at CorroHealth.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Leading RCM Innovation Across Borders</strong></p><p>The partnership is expected to accelerate SANTECHTURE’s momentum across the Middle East, where demand for tech-forward healthcare solutions is on the rise. With AI at the core of its model, the company is positioned to deliver on both cost containment and revenue optimization, helping healthcare providers navigate the pressures of modern care delivery.&nbsp;</p><blockquote><p>“It’s about combining the best of both worlds—local expertise and global AI innovation—to reshape how revenue cycle management is delivered in this region,”&nbsp;</p></blockquote><p>added CorroHealth CEO Pat Leonard.</p>	\N	{Launch}	https://cdn.wamda.com/feature-images/5d28a490613a50c.jpg	0	0	{"byline": "Abu Dhabi SME Hub", "author_bio": null, "author_org": null, "author_name": "Abu Dhabi SME Hub", "author_title": null, "author_photo_url": null}	\N	2025-11-11 13:17:01.719153+00	2025-11-14 10:04:40.912628+00	\N	\N	https://cdn.wamda.com/feature-images/5d28a490613a50c.jpg	\N	\N	0	{"likes": 0, "views": 0, "comments": 0}	\N	\N	corrohealth-backs-uaes-santechture-to-drive-ai-led-transformation-in-healthcare-revenue-management	\N	{}	f	\N	\N	{}	\N	\N	\N	{}	\N	\N	\N	\N	0	0	\N
