77c31875-0d55-4cbb-a06b-b85708fdd145	Yango Group Unveils $20 Million Venture Fund to Accelerate Startup Grow	Article	\N	\N	Published	2025-10-09 20:25:41.068+00	<p>UAE-based tech ecosystem company Yango Group has introduced <strong>Yango Ventures</strong>, a $20 million corporate venture fund aimed at fueling the growth of innovative startups across key global markets. The fund will provide capital and strategic support to promising early-stage companies in LATAM, Sub-Saharan Africa, MENAP, and other high-potential regions.</p><p>Yango Ventures will focus on startups from <strong>Seed to Series B</strong> that are transforming the <strong>O2O (Online-to-Offline), B2B SaaS, and fintech</strong> sectors. In addition to financial investment, the fund will offer entrepreneurs access to Yango Group’s extensive expertise, global network, and market insights to help scale their businesses and create lasting economic impact.</p><p><em>"We’re not just investing in technology—we’re investing in people and communities. Yango Ventures is an extension of our commitment to empowering entrepreneurs with the tools, knowledge, and connections they need to succeed,"</em> said <strong>Daniil Shuleyko, CEO of Yango Group</strong>. <em>"By fostering innovation in high-growth regions, we aim to support local talent and drive sustainable business expansion that benefits entire economies."</em></p><p>While initially launching with a $20 million fund, Yango Ventures is structured for scalability, with plans to expand its investment capacity in response to the evolving needs of the startup ecosystem. The fund’s goal is to <strong>promote digital transformation</strong> and support businesses that are shaping the future of fintech, mobility, entertainment, AI, and other technology-driven industries.</p><p>Backing Yango Ventures is a team of experienced professionals with a proven track record of <strong>scaling B2B SaaS and B2C technology platforms</strong> across various industries. Their expertise in building and expanding businesses globally will provide founders with critical mentorship, strategic insights, and operational guidance.</p><p>Yango Ventures is part of Yango Group’s broader initiative to drive digital transformation and <strong>strengthen local innovation ecosystems</strong>. In addition to funding startups, the company actively supports entrepreneurial communities through <strong>networking events, educational partnerships, and skill-building initiatives</strong> designed to equip future innovators with practical knowledge and industry connections.</p><p>With this latest initiative, Yango Group reaffirms its commitment to <strong>harnessing technology for global progress</strong>, helping startups turn groundbreaking ideas into scalable, impactful solutions.</p>		{Article}	https://cdn.wamda.com/feature-images/ac52abbcbb8d301.jpg	0	0	{"body_json": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"text": "UAE-based tech ecosystem company Yango Group has introduced ", "type": "text"}, {"text": "Yango Ventures", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"text": ", a $20 million corporate venture fund aimed at fueling the growth of innovative startups across key global markets. The fund will provide capital and strategic support to promising early-stage companies in LATAM, Sub-Saharan Africa, MENAP, and other high-potential regions.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"text": "Yango Ventures will focus on startups from ", "type": "text"}, {"text": "Seed to Series B", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"text": " that are transforming the ", "type": "text"}, {"text": "O2O (Online-to-Offline), B2B SaaS, and fintech", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"text": " sectors. In addition to financial investment, the fund will offer entrepreneurs access to Yango Group’s extensive expertise, global network, and market insights to help scale their businesses and create lasting economic impact.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"text": "\\"We’re not just investing in technology—we’re investing in people and communities. Yango Ventures is an extension of our commitment to empowering entrepreneurs with the tools, knowledge, and connections they need to succeed,\\"", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}]}, {"text": " said ", "type": "text"}, {"text": "Daniil Shuleyko, CEO of Yango Group", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"text": ". ", "type": "text"}, {"text": "\\"By fostering innovation in high-growth regions, we aim to support local talent and drive sustainable business expansion that benefits entire economies.\\"", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"text": "While initially launching with a $20 million fund, Yango Ventures is structured for scalability, with plans to expand its investment capacity in response to the evolving needs of the startup ecosystem. The fund’s goal is to ", "type": "text"}, {"text": "promote digital transformation", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"text": " and support businesses that are shaping the future of fintech, mobility, entertainment, AI, and other technology-driven industries.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"text": "Backing Yango Ventures is a team of experienced professionals with a proven track record of ", "type": "text"}, {"text": "scaling B2B SaaS and B2C technology platforms", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"text": " across various industries. Their expertise in building and expanding businesses globally will provide founders with critical mentorship, strategic insights, and operational guidance.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"text": "Yango Ventures is part of Yango Group’s broader initiative to drive digital transformation and ", "type": "text"}, {"text": "strengthen local innovation ecosystems", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"text": ". In addition to funding startups, the company actively supports entrepreneurial communities through ", "type": "text"}, {"text": "networking events, educational partnerships, and skill-building initiatives", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"text": " designed to equip future innovators with practical knowledge and industry connections.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"text": "With this latest initiative, Yango Group reaffirms its commitment to ", "type": "text"}, {"text": "harnessing technology for global progress", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"text": ", helping startups turn groundbreaking ideas into scalable, impactful solutions.", "type": "text"}]}]}}	\N	2025-10-09 20:25:37.558+00	2025-10-28 12:22:07.74684+00	\N	\N	https://cdn.wamda.com/feature-images/ac52abbcbb8d301.jpg	\N	\N	0	{"likes": 0, "views": 0, "comments": 0}	\N	\N	yango-group-unveils-20-million-venture-fund-to-accelerate-startup-grow	\N	{}	f	\N	\N	{}	\N	\N	\N	{}	\N	\N	\N	\N	0	0	\N
3d794fbd-1b18-46d5-be04-9d564e88a220	WaHa secures $8mln in Series A-1 funding to accelerate global growth 	Article	\N	Abu Dhabi SME Hub	Published	2025-10-10 00:00:00+00	<p>This financing eliminates all debt, simplifies WaHa’s cap table, and provides capital for the company to achieve its next major commercial milestones and close its next funding round.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Water Harvesting Inc. (WaHa) announced the close of an $8 million Series A-1 financing and corporate reorganization. The round was led by Chairman Mike Phillips and Board member Christian Thirion, with participation from WaHa’s largest noteholders and investors including Berkeley Catalyst Fund, Anthropocene Institute, Vestafund, and Mitsui Mining &amp; Smelting Co., Ltd.</p><p>This financing eliminates all debt, simplifies WaHa’s cap table, and provides capital for the company to achieve its next major commercial milestones and close its next funding round. It also supports a growing pipeline of qualified sales opportunities across the UAE and GCC, where field trials at Khalifa University have proven its unique ability to harvest pure water reliably in the UAE’s harsh desert environment of extreme heat, low moisture, and frequent sandstorms.</p><p>Since 2023, WaHa’s atmospheric water generation (AWG) systems have been deployed in challenging environments including West Texas, Abu Dhabi, a remote UAE desert site, Riyadh, and Stockholm. These systems have achieved 99.998% mechanical reliability and produced 98.3% of target water volume—the highest sustained output in the AWG industry. The company’s 14 patent families, with 18 patents granted worldwide, protect its proprietary WaHa Vaporator® technology, a modular system supporting off-grid installations and integration with HVAC and agricultural systems.</p><p>WaHa will unveil its first commercially available AWG unit at the WETEX 2025 exhibition in Dubai (September 30 – October 2), showcasing solutions for utilities, developers, and industrial operators seeking reliable, sustainable access to pure water.</p><blockquote><p>“We’ve built a platform capable of transforming access to water across multiple sectors,”&nbsp;</p></blockquote><p>said Mike Phillips, Chairman, WaHa.&nbsp;</p><blockquote><p>“This raise will enable us to establish solid traction for the WaHa Vaporator® and improve water security in the UAE and broader GCC.”</p></blockquote><blockquote><p>“We’re grateful for the support of our investors and partners,”&nbsp;</p></blockquote><p>added Frank Ramirez, CEO of WaHa.&nbsp;</p><blockquote><p>“This is a major step toward delivering water where it’s needed most—reliably, efficiently, and sustainably. We’re proud of what our team has achieved and energized for what’s ahead.”</p></blockquote><p>WaHa is negotiating commercial agreements for manufacturing, distribution, and long-term service and support.</p>		{Growth}	https://static.zawya.com/view/acePublic/alias/contentid/5f3edb23-cf02-45a6-8a2b-0291dc89c2c5/0/frankramirez-ceoofwaha-jpg.webp?f=3%3A2&q=0.75&w=1080	0	0	{"byline": "Abu Dhabi SME Hub", "author_bio": null, "author_org": null, "author_name": "Abu Dhabi SME Hub", "author_title": null, "author_photo_url": null}	\N	2025-10-10 06:12:42.565+00	2025-11-13 07:09:15.069138+00	\N	\N	https://static.zawya.com/view/acePublic/alias/contentid/5f3edb23-cf02-45a6-8a2b-0291dc89c2c5/0/frankramirez-ceoofwaha-jpg.webp?f=3%3A2&q=0.75&w=1080	\N	\N	0	{"likes": 0, "views": 0, "comments": 0}	\N	\N	waha-secures-8mln-in-series-a-1-funding-to-accelerate-global-growth	\N	{}	f	\N	\N	{}	\N	\N	\N	{}	\N	\N	\N	\N	0	0	\N
8903cebf-a937-4bc9-84cc-1265b5fe3aac	Why is having problems a good thing for aspiring entrepreneurs?	Video	\N	\N	Published	2025-10-09 21:06:01.329+00	\N	The story of Airbnb is rich in anecdotes on problems that, on closer look, revealed themselves as opportunities in disguise. By simply going through the problem step-by-step, they recognized the asset value of their own real estate under certain conditions, coupled with their ability to provide competitive prices.\n\nA key takeaway for aspiring entrepreneurs is to reframe their mindset towards problems - especially those with existing market solutions – to perceive those as opportunities and to research methods to address said gaps.	{Video}	https://www.thesmallbusinesssite.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/questions.jpg	0	0	{}	\N	2025-10-09 21:05:50.134+00	2025-10-28 12:22:07.74684+00	\N	\N	https://www.thesmallbusinesssite.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/questions.jpg	\N	353	0	{"likes": 0, "views": 0, "comments": 0}	\N	\N	why-is-having-problems-a-good-thing-for-aspiring-entrepreneurs	\N	{}	f	https://kfmediaitems.blob.core.windows.net/mediaitems/video/8903cebf-a937-4bc9-84cc-1265b5fe3aac/1760043950850-why-is-having-problems-a-good-thing-for-aspiring-entrepreneurs.mp4	\N	{}	\N	\N	\N	{}	\N	\N	\N	\N	0	0	\N
