mpany`s internal capabilities but on how well it integrates into the larger community ecosystem. The notion that SMEs can achieve success by working in isolation is outdated. Businesses must embrace community involvement as a strategic pillar, cultivating relationships, collaborating with industry players, and engaging with the broader societal ecosystem. The companies that will thrive in the future are those that not only leverage external resources but also contribute to the collective growth of their communities. ", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"text": "In conclusion, SMEs in Abu Dhabi are poised to unlock new growth potential by embracing the power of community. Networking, mentorship, and collaboration are no longer just tools for survival—they are the strategic levers that will define success in the future. To truly drive innovation and long-term growth, SMEs must view community engagement as a core business function, aligning their goals with the broader ecosystem to create a sustainable, competitive advantage. The time has come for SMEs to rethink their approach: Communities don’t just support growth; they are the engine driving it.", "type": "text"}]}]}}	\N	2025-10-01 17:53:48.456321+00	2025-10-28 12:22:07.74684+00	\N	\N	https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9c/Abu_dhabi_skylines_2014.jpg/500px-Abu_dhabi_skylines_2014.jpg	\N	\N	0	{"likes": 0, "views": 0, "comments": 0}	\N	\N	how-communities-drive-sme-growth-in-abu-dhabi	\N	{}	f	\N	\N	{}	\N	\N	\N	{}	\N	\N	\N	\N	0	0	\N
