afb0653b-df53-4884-a128-252b3d1a4401	Google Announces Second "AI First" Accelerator for Startups in Middle East, North Africa, and Turkiye 	Article	\N	Abu Dhabi SME Hub	Published	\N	<p>The 12-week, equity-free program is designed to empower the most promising Seed to Series A startups that are harnessing the power of artificial intelligence, providing them with the essential infrastructure, tools, and expertise to scale and succeed.<br><br>Google announced the launch of its second "Google for Startups Accelerator: AI First" program for the Middle East, North Africa, and Turkiye (MENA-T). The 12-week, equity-free program is designed to empower the most promising Seed to Series A startups that are harnessing the power of artificial intelligence, providing them with the essential infrastructure, tools, and expertise to scale and succeed.</p><p>The MENA-T region is rapidly emerging as a significant hub for AI innovation, driving transformative change across various industries. Highlighting this potential, PwC estimates AI could contribute $15.7 trillion to the global economy by 2030, with McKinsey projecting up to $150 billion for GCC countries alone. Regional AI investment is also accelerating, with its share of total startup funding more than doubling year-over-year from 2023 to 2024, according to Wamda reports. PwC further expects the region to accrue US$320 billion, or 2 percent of the total global benefits of AI, by 2030.</p><blockquote><p>"The incredible momentum of AI development in the Middle East, North Africa, and Turkiye region presents a unique opportunity to foster a new wave of technological advancement,"&nbsp;</p></blockquote><p>said Abdul Rahman Al Thehaiban, Managing Director, MENA-T, Google Cloud.&nbsp;</p><blockquote><p>"Google Cloud is committed to providing a robust and scalable platform for AI innovation. Our aim is to equip these pioneering companies with the cloud infrastructure and expertise necessary to optimize their AI workloads and accelerate their growth trajectory in this dynamic field."</p></blockquote><p>Anthony Nakache, Managing Director, Google MENA, said:&nbsp;</p><blockquote><p>''With the 'Google for Startups Accelerator: AI First' program, we are dedicated to providing targeted support to innovative startups, helping them access Google's best resources to solve complex challenges and scale their impactful AI-driven solutions globally."</p></blockquote><p>The "Google for Startups Accelerator: AI First" MENA-T program provides selected eligible startups with Google Cloud credits to accelerate the development and deployment of their AI solutions. Participants will benefit from expert technical mentorship from Google Cloud engineers and solution architects to optimize cloud infrastructure for AI workloads. The program also includes AI-focused workshops on Google Cloud's AI/ML capabilities, data analytics, and serverless computing, alongside workshops on Go-To-Market strategies covering product design, business growth, and leadership development. Crucially, the accelerator will offer extensive networking opportunities with a curated network of investors, potential partners, and industry leaders.</p><p>Seed to Series A startups in the MENA-T region building AI-first solutions are encouraged to apply for the "Google for Startups Accelerator: AI First" MENA-T program by June 16th, 2025, through the Google for Startups website.</p>	\N	{Launch}	https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!HQmx!,w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fae9ffe74-bee0-4445-a89e-075d3e4f4229_1280x720.png	0	0	{"byline": "Abu Dhabi SME Hub", "author_bio": null, "author_org": null, "author_name": "Abu Dhabi SME Hub", "author_title": null, "author_photo_url": null}	\N	2025-11-12 12:17:26.53229+00	2025-11-12 12:17:52.266398+00	\N	\N	https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!HQmx!,w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fae9ffe74-bee0-4445-a89e-075d3e4f4229_1280x720.png	\N	\N	0	{"likes": 0, "views": 0, "comments": 0}	\N	\N	google-announces-second-ai-first-accelerator-for-startups-in-middle-east-north-africa-and-turkiye	\N	{}	f	\N	\N	{}	\N	\N	\N	{}	\N	\N	\N	\N	0	0	\N
7404840a-2068-4166-82aa-4ac402968df0	Roomz.rent Raises Pre-Seed Round to Redefine Co-Living	Article	\N	Abu Dhabi SME Hub	Published	2025-11-14 09:33:50.988+00	<p>Since launching in November 2024, the platform has sold over $100,000 worth of contracts.<br><br>Roomz.rent has successfully raised a pre-seed funding round led by Qora71 (Hub71-based angel investor syndicate) and other angel investors. Born in Cairo, Roomz.rent is the region’s first co-living platform, providing hassle-free, affordable, and flexible long-term room rentals starting from just 3 months. By intelligently matching tenants with ideal flatmates and offering fully managed accommodations, Roomz.rent addresses the common struggles faced by renters in urban cities, such as high rental costs, rigid lease terms, and the difficulty of finding compatible flatmates.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Since launching in November 2024, the platform has sold over $100,000 worth of contracts in under 5 months, with an average stay of 9 months per contract. Roomz.rent is on a mission to scale Cairo first, then expand across the region one city at a time, bringing a smarter way of living to urban centers across MENA.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Beyond convenience, Roomz.rent is driving real societal impact by helping young professionals, expats, and students cut their rental costs in half, without compromising on comfort, privacy, or quality of living.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Mohamed Ayman, CEO:&nbsp;</p><blockquote><p>“We’re aiming to make city living more accessible to everyone. Roomz.rent create a new standard of urban living, one where flexibility, community, and affordability come built-in. Cairo is just the beginning.”</p></blockquote><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Youssef Salem, Director of Qora71:&nbsp;</p><blockquote><p>“Roomz.rent is tackling one of the biggest and most broken categories in MENA, urban rentals. It is a unique blend of real estate operations, tech-enabled matching, and cultural relevance. In just months, they’ve shown traction and discipline we usually see at a later stage than pre-seed.”</p></blockquote>	\N	{Launch}	https://arabfounders.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/roomz.jpg	0	0	{"byline": "Abu Dhabi SME Hub", "author_bio": null, "author_org": null, "author_name": "Abu Dhabi SME Hub", "author_title": null, "author_photo_url": null}	\N	2025-11-11 11:36:27.907451+00	2025-11-14 09:33:52.784385+00	\N	\N	https://arabfounders.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/roomz.jpg	\N	\N	0	{"likes": 0, "views": 0, "comments": 0}	\N	\N	roomzrent-raises-pre-seed-round-to-redefine-co-living	\N	{}	f	\N	\N	{}	\N	\N	\N	{}	\N	\N	\N	\N	0	0	\N
