08a8dd64-b56f-4eda-95d0-a1e3daafbb60	Middle East investors Summit to host first-of-its-kind family office initiative 	Article	\N	Abu Dhabi SME Hub	Published	\N	<p>It is the first time direct, world-class investment in the upskilling of family offices has been made available in the Middle East.<br><br>The Middle East Investors Summit - Abu Dhabi edition, the region’s premier gathering of institutional investors, family offices and innovators from around the world, returns to the Rosewood Abu Dhabi from 27-28 May 2025.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Presented in partnership with the Emirates Family Office Association (EFOA) and NYU Abu Dhabi as the Summit’s academic partner, the Summit’s 2025 edition will host an interactive program for family office leaders and investment professionals titled ‘The Middle East Wealth &amp; Investment Leadership program’.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>The prestigious entities will combine to host immersive, interactive sessions for participants - in a first-of-its-kind initiative. Families and investment professionals will be equipped with tools to strengthen their network, perfect their leadership skills and further sophisticate their operations.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>It is the first time direct, world-class investment in the upskilling of family offices has been made available in the Middle East.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Adam Ladjadj, Founder and Vice Chairman, Emirates Family Office Association, said:</p><p>&nbsp;</p><blockquote><p>“This innovative program at Middle East Investors Summit reinforces the Association’s commitment to excellence in family office governance and sophistication. We are proud to partner and share this vision with one of the world’s leading universities - NYU Abu Dhabi - at an event showcasing the UAE’s flourishing business and financial environment."</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>“I look forward to welcoming the program’s first cohort as we help families make better decisions in preserving and growing their wealth; modernizing their business structures and scaling their operations internationally.”</p></blockquote><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Amol Dani, Chief Operating Officer, NYU Abu Dhabi, said:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><blockquote><p>“We are very proud to collaborate with the Emirates Family Office Association on this first-of-its-kind initiative. At NYU Abu Dhabi, we believe in the power of education to drive meaningful change, and this program is a great example of that. It brings together our academic expertise with the practical needs of today’s investment and family office landscape, creating a space for learning, connection, and real impact.”</p></blockquote><p>&nbsp;</p><p>All EFOA-sponsored program participants will be active contributors in an environment geared to rich learning, connections, and insights. Participants will also receive an NYU Abu Dhabi certification on completion.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Hosted by Collab, the Summit and its program are geared to high-level business figures; leading investors and family office professionals passionate about face-to-face interactions, debate, knowledge-sharing and connectivity – amid the backdrop of the Middle East’s thriving financial landscape.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>The Summit’s welcoming keynote will be given by H.E. Dr. Ahmed Al Banna, Chairman of the Emirates Family Office Association, with sessions to follow exploring topics including changing UAE / GCC regulatory frameworks as drivers of new investment opportunities and how SWFs are navigating uncertainty amidst the rapidly changing geopolitical landscape.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Those in the family office and investment sectors, in the UAE and internationally, who are interested in the program and in becoming a member of EFOA can find out more by contacting <a href="mailto:info@emiratesfoa.com">mailto:info@emiratesfoa.com</a>.</p>	\N	{Launch}	https://static.zawya.com/view/acePublic/alias/contentid/85d50a55-5b49-4f2f-82df-58b12f8ea9e4/0/meisad-image-jpg.webp?f=3%3A2&q=0.75&w=1080	0	0	{"byline": "Abu Dhabi SME Hub", "author_bio": null, "author_org": null, "author_name": "Abu Dhabi SME Hub", "author_title": null, "author_photo_url": null}	\N	2025-11-12 11:49:25.557813+00	2025-11-12 11:49:46.31385+00	\N	\N	https://static.zawya.com/view/acePublic/alias/contentid/85d50a55-5b49-4f2f-82df-58b12f8ea9e4/0/meisad-image-jpg.webp?f=3%3A2&q=0.75&w=1080	\N	\N	0	{"likes": 0, "views": 0, "comments": 0}	\N	\N	middle-east-investors-summit-to-host-first-of-its-kind-family-office-initiative	\N	{}	f	\N	\N	{}	\N	\N	\N	{}	\N	\N	\N	\N	0	0	\N
576fca37-ffa5-4929-a0de-320bb6b7104c	Tarjama Secures $15M Series A to Scale Arabic AI Ecosystem, Led by Global Ventures with Wamda Capital Participation	Article	\N	Abu Dhabi SME Hub	Published	\N	<p>Founded in 2009 by Nour Al Hassan, Tarjama has become a regional leader in Arabic-first AI, powering language solutions across 50+ languages and 22 Arabic dialects for more than 700 global clients.<br><br>UAE-based language technology company Tarjama has raised $15 million in a Series A funding round, led by Global Ventures and joined by Wamda Capital, TA Ventures, Phaze Capital, Golden Gate Ventures, and Endeavor Catalyst.</p><p>Founded in 2009 by Nour Al Hassan, Tarjama has become a regional leader in Arabic-first AI, powering language solutions across 50+ languages and 22 Arabic dialects for more than 700 global clients.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Powering the Arabic AI Revolution</strong></p><p>This funding round will fuel the growth of Arabic.AI, Tarjama’s enterprise-focused agentic AI ecosystem built specifically for Arabic-speaking markets. The platform is powered by Pronoia V2, a purpose-built Arabic Large Language Model (LLM) that already outperforms major global models like GPT-4o, Cohere, and DeepSeek-V3 on Arabic tasks.&nbsp;</p><blockquote><p>“Arabic has been underserved by AI for far too long,”&nbsp;</p></blockquote><p>said Nour Al Hassan, Founder and CEO of Tarjama.&nbsp;</p><blockquote><p>“Our flagship model, Pronoia, is faster, more secure, and more cost-effective than any other solution on the market. It’s built for the realities of Arabic language, culture, and enterprise demands—and we’re just getting started.”</p></blockquote><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Scaling for the Agentic AI Era</strong></p><p>The funds will be used to:</p><ul><li>Double the size of Tarjama’s engineering and research teams</li><li>Expand sovereign infrastructure across MENA</li><li>Launch an AI Academy to upskill enterprise and government leaders in Arabic-speaking countries</li></ul><p>With a deep understanding of local dialects, business context, and cultural nuance, Tarjama is uniquely positioned to lead the shift to agentic AI systems in a region with over 400 million Arabic speakers and a $3 trillion digital economy. Said Murad, Senior Partner at Global Ventures, commented:&nbsp;“Tarjama’s technology and traction are remarkable. Pronoia is a true market leader, purpose-built for a region where generic AI tools have consistently fallen short. We’re proud to support this next chapter of scale.”</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Profitable Growth and Global Potential</strong></p><p>Tarjama is already profitable and has reported 20% CAGR in revenue over the past three years. With a proprietary dataset unmatched in Arabic AI, and a rapidly growing product suite, the company is poised to become a global benchmark for enterprise-grade, Arabic-first AI. With new backing from top-tier investors and a fast-expanding AI ecosystem, Tarjama is rewriting what’s possible in Arabic language technology—equipping enterprises to move faster, smarter, and more locally fluent in one of the world’s most dynamic markets.</p>	\N	{Growth}	https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!ei6g!,w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd5c86a77-cf3c-40ac-bde2-5772652dbe38_1280x721.png	0	0	{"byline": "Abu Dhabi SME Hub", "author_bio": null, "author_org": null, "author_name": "Abu Dhabi SME Hub", "author_title": null, "author_photo_url": null}	\N	2025-11-12 11:24:04.303753+00	2025-11-12 11:24:53.814045+00	\N	\N	https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!ei6g!,w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd5c86a77-cf3c-40ac-bde2-5772652dbe38_1280x721.png	\N	\N	0	{"likes": 0, "views": 0, "comments": 0}	\N	\N	tarjama-secures-15m-series-a-to-scale-arabic-ai-ecosystem-led-by-global-ventures-with-wamda-capital-participation	\N	{}	f